@Justice1337- it's not a specific deck, but the fact that the most powerful cards are Blue and Black.  
Look at the Vintage Restricted list- you won't find much Red, Green, or White.  

[Ancestral Recall](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancestral Recall), [Time Walk](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Time Walk), [Timetwister](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Timetwister), [Necropotence](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Necropotence), [Yawgmoth's Will](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Yawgmoth's Will), [Yawgmoth's Bargain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Yawgmoth's Bargain), [Demonic Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Tutor), [Tinker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tinker), etc. are cards \*many\* people want to use in their Vintage decks.  

@Claybird- you're right about a one-in-a-million find;  
Booster packs up until Ice Age/4th were semi-transparent,  
and the less scrupulous resellers can cheat   
and make sure the boosters they sell don't contain anything valuable.

